                draw on a long tradition of extreme intolerance within one stream of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Islam</ENAMEX> (a
                minority tradition), from <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">at least</NUMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Ibn Taimiyyah</ENAMEX>, through the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">founders</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Wahhabism</ENAMEX>,
                through the <ENAMEX TYPE="LAW">Muslim Brotherhood, to Sayyid Qutb</ENAMEX>. That stream is motivated by religion
                and does not distinguish politics from religion, thus distorting both. It is further
                <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">fed</ENAMEX> by grievances stressed by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bin Ladin</ENAMEX> and widely felt throughout the <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">Muslim</ENAMEX>
