            <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Islam</ENAMEX> is not the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">enemy</ENAMEX>. It is not synonymous with terror. Nor does Islam teach
                terror. <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">America</ENAMEX> and its <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">friends</ENAMEX> oppose a perversion of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Islam</ENAMEX>, not the great world
                faith itself. Lives guided by religious faith, including literal beliefs in holy
                scriptures, are common to every religion, and represent no threat to us. Other
                religions have experienced violent internal struggles. With so many diverse
                adherents, every major religion will spawn violent zealots. Yet understanding and
                tolerance among <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">people</ENAMEX> of different faiths can and must prevail. The present
                transnational danger is <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Islamist</ENAMEX> terrorism. What is needed is a broad
                <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">political-military</ENAMEX> strategy that rests on a firm tripod of policies to
            
                attack <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">terrorists</ENAMEX> and their <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">organizations</ENAMEX>;
                prevent the continued growth of <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Islamist</ENAMEX> terrorism; and
